Radisson Blu Hotel, Dubai Media City, requires a professional, responsible, pro-active service oriented individuals who believe in keeping promises and delivering the same with an attitude of Yes I Can! and Z-factor for the position of F&D; Administrator for our Kitchen Department.
Primary Objective of Position
Under the general guidance of the Executive Chef, evaluate and ensure that long-term and short-term goals of Kitchen department are met. To assist in directing and managing all Kitchen activities. To ensure that all work will be in line with the hotel’s guidelines and business plan and Radisson Blu corporate guidelines and service concepts.
F&D; administrator’s job entails providing administrative support on day-to-day basis and contributing to the long-run development of Kitchen function.
Duties and Responsibilities
• Record keeping of all day to day activities
• Set up all filing system & maintaining of files
• Responsible for coordinating all the HACCP activities.
• Maintains SOP’s and take care of all the administrative responsibilities
• Responsible for typing all outgoing correspondence, proof-read and distribute to concerned persons
• Handles all incoming and outgoing mails.
• Coordinating among all sections of Food & Drinks
• Answer telephone calls as per the hotel standard.
• Attend meetings and take minutes whenever required.
• All other secretarial works relevant to the department
• Distributing of info to departments & sections
• Flexible working hours to be handled
• Motivate & support techniques available to help subordinates to achieve their departmental targets.
• Responsible for planning of training and development of employees in order to minimize staff turnover,
• Utilizes leadership skills and motivation to maximize employee productivity and
Satisfaction
• With Executive Chef, maintains an updated recipe file.
• Monitors department’s overall service and team work daily, and makes recommendations for improvement if required.
Personal Requirements
The successful candidate will be a highly motivated, dynamic, enthusiastic individual with a creative flair You will have a minimum of two years experience in a similar style of operation. Willingness to learn and adapt to new ideas and concepts Fluent in English Thrives on taking responsibility and working in an empowered environment Hungry for personal development Team player
'
